{{short description|An international project to investigate deep-water biology of the Scotia and Weddell seas}} The '''''Antarctic Benthic Deep-Sea Biodiversity Project (ANDEEP)'''''<ref>http://www.cedamar.org/ANDEEP</ref> is an international project to investigate deep-water biology of the Scotia and Weddell seas. [[Benthic]] refers to "bottom-dwelling" organisms that are known to exhibit unusual characteristics not normally seen in shallow-dwelling creatures. ANDEEP has already made many notable discoveries, such as animals with gigantism and extraordinary longevity.<ref>http://www.sams.ac.uk/research/departments/biogeochemistry-department/biogeochmistry-projects/researchproject.2007-04-23.8241548381</ref>
